## Security Audit Approval

All 10 security findings from the initial audit have been successfully addressed:

### HIGH Priority (RESOLVED ✅)
- HIGH-001: Webhook URL Validation - Data exfiltration risk

### MEDIUM Priority (RESOLVED ✅)
- MED-001: Resolver Identity Verification - Impersonation attacks
- MED-002: Resolver Reason Sanitization - Audit log injection
- MED-003: Webhook Response Validation - Silent notification failures
- MED-004: Audit Trail HMAC Signatures - Tampering risk
- MED-005: Storage Trust Model Documentation - Unclear trust assumptions

### LOW Priority (RESOLVED ✅)
- LOW-001: MfaVerifier Error Contract - Ambiguous error handling
- LOW-002: Error Message Sanitization - Network topology leakage
- LOW-003: Terraform Plan Display Sanitization - XSS risk
- LOW-004: Race Condition on Expiration - TOCTOU race (ACKNOWLEDGED)

